26/10/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Gheorghe Flutur, deputy leader of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party, announced on Monday (October 25th) that all lawmakers from the ruling party and its partners at the Democratic Alliance of Hungarians (UDMR) will abstain from Wednesday's planned no-confidence vote against the government. 
The move increases the government's chances of surviving the vote The cabinet hopes the decision will help it maintain discipline among its lawmakers, some of whom may be tempted to support the motion in the anonymous voting. 
The opposition has 213 members in parliament and needs another 23 votes to achieve a majority in the 470-seat parliament. 
The opposition filed the motion the austerity measures undertaken by the government. 
(Reuters, Evenimentul Zilei, Hotnews.ro, Realitatea - 25/10/10)
